Phase 1: Deployment & Infrastructure (Critical)
Deploy to Linera Testnet

Start a local Linera validator or connect to a public testnet
Deploy both traditional-leagues and coindrafts-core applications
Get application IDs and chain IDs for frontend integration
Frontend Connection Setup

Configure the Svelte frontend to connect to deployed applications
Set up GraphQL endpoints for queries and mutations
Test basic connectivity and data fetching
Phase 2: Core User Experience
Basic UI Flow Implementation

Create Game → Join Tournament → Submit Portfolio → View Results
Tournament listing and status display
Portfolio creation interface with crypto selection
Wallet Integration

Connect Linera wallet for user authentication
Enable transaction signing for operations
Handle wallet connection states and errors
Phase 3: Real-time Features
Live Updates
Tournament countdown timers
Player count updates
Live leaderboards and results
Tournament status changes (Registration → In Progress → Completed)
Phase 4: Testing Preparation
Demo Data & Scenarios

Pre-created tournaments for immediate testing
Sample portfolios with different risk profiles
Mock price data for realistic scoring
Cross-chain Verification

Test message flow: CoinDrafts Core ↔ Traditional Leagues
Verify tournament creation, player registration, and completion
Check portfolio synchronization and winner calculation
User Testing Setup

Test user accounts with some USDC tokens
User guides and onboarding flow
Feedback collection system (forms, analytics)